race.comment: SHUTTLE RUN (1) bounced back to form here last start in this grade. Murtagh sticks and he's well placed to build on his strong association. FLYING STEP (7) resumes for her new stable and showed solid staying efforts last prep over longer trips. This is well short of her ideal distance, but if the tempo is strong enough she can be the one charging late. SOLAR GAZE (2) was too sharp for a maiden field over 1000m here last time. Now that he's put it together, he deserves respect. TI TREE ROYAL (6) can mix his form but his best figures stack up. From the middle draw he should blend in nicely and is one of the winning chances.
